In commemoration of the annual armed forces remembrance day celebration, former governor of Anambra state, Peter Obi has commiserated with the families of fallen heroes, as he extolled their bravery. He made this known on his official twitter handle, @peterobi, today, stating that hopefully their sacrifices wont go in vain. He wrote, “Thank you for committing yourselves to our country’s safety. On this Armed Forces Remembrance Day, I join millions of appreciative citizens in acknowledging your sacrifices. My prayer is that those sacrifices shall not be in vain. – PO #ArmedForcesRememberanceDay.” RED ALERT: New Ransomware Attacking Organisational Networks… I Endorsed Tinubu For Presidency In 2019, I Have Rejected Him… See tweet below; Thank you for committing yourselves to our country’s safety. On this Armed Forces Remembrance Day, I join millions of appreciative citizens in acknowledging your sacrifices. My prayer is that those sacrifices shall not be in vain. – PO#ArmedForcesRememberanceDay